    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8221" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥέζω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝρ., ϝέργον</span>), ipf. iter. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥέζεσκον</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥέξω</span>, aor.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔρεξα, ἔρρεξε, ῥέξε</span>, subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥέξομεν</span>, pass. aor. inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥεχθῆναι</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥεχθείς</span>, cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔρδω</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">do, work, act</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μέγα ἔργον,
            εὖ</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κακῶς τινά,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 23.56</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> οὐ
            κατὰ μοῖραν ἔρεξας</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            9.352</span></i>; pass., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥεχθέν δέ τε νήπιος
            ἔγνω</span>, ‘a thing once done,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
            17.32</span></i>; esp., ‘do’ sacrifice, ‘perform,’ ‘offer,’ ‘sacrifice,’
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἑκατόμβην, θαλύ̄σια</span>, abs. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θεῷ</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 9.
            535</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 8.250</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
